comments.body:
Right now, there is no real plans to create a rendered view for watchOS. This is due to low demand and also, no easy way to create a watchOS view. Typically, the SkiaSharp views derive from some `UIView` or OpenGL view, but none exist on the watch.

I did some looking around and I found that people just created a `UIImage` and then used an image view to display it. You can do the same with SkiaSharp and the `SkiaSharp.Views.watchOS` namespace extension methods:

```csharp
// sue normal SkiaSharp
var bitmap = new SKBitmap(100, 100);
// … draw …

// use the extension methods to convert the SkiaSharp image to a watchOS image
var image = bitmap.ToUIImage(…);

// display
imageView.SetImage(image);
```

I have a full sample here: https://github.com/mono/SkiaSharp/blob/v1.60.3/samples/Basic/watchOS/SkiaSharpSample.OnWatchExtension/InterfaceController.cs
